TWO people were killed and five seriously injured after a taxi collided with a light motor vehicle at the intersection of Nelson Mandela and Oliver Tambo Drives in Secunda, Mpumalanga on Saturday, 4 June. ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said paramedics were on the scene at about 11pm along with the fire department, police and other private services. “An adult male was found in the driver’s seat of the light motor vehicle showing no signs of life. “He was declared dead on arrival. An adult female was found inside the taxi also showing no signs of life and was also declared dead on arrival by ER24,” Meiring said in a statement. ALSO READ: Two killed, one injured in car crash He said five other adult patients suffered serious injuries. “Four of them were lying on the road, having been ejected from the taxi. “Advanced Life Support interventions were required to stabilise the injured before they were transported to Evander Hospital for further care,” Meiring added. 